er_search_telemetry_sources.js.  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295230\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295475\n", "files": ["browser/components/search/test/browser/telemetry/browser_search_telemetry_sources.js"], "git_node": "564d8e2f4e28dcf0529086f6a2b095bdd79e62d1", "git_parents": ["93fb5c04518398a08d5f8b64daf1f56c1e7caec6"], "node": "ed669ba8f6614024b5243255f3c47ba9050ff92f", "parents": ["6c2652e93ff5c8e0252c3a59b0b9903e18f0a145"], "tags": []}], "date": 1776774284, "git_changesets": ["564d8e2f4e28dcf0529086f6a2b095bdd79e62d1"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25840": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1964551 - [devtools] Fix race condition in browser_net_overrides_with_debugger.js  a=dmeehan\n\nWhen reviewing https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288166 I noticed the order between `await waitForSetOverride;` and `await writeTextContentToPath(OVERRIDDEN_SCRIPT, path);` was the opposite of our other helper, but I didn't think this could matter.\n\nIt's actually critical to wait until `waitForSetOverride` is complete, because this action will attempt to write the file once, with the initial content from the response.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295404\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295503\n", "files": ["devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_overrides_with_debugger.js"], "git_node": "929b3f8b7279019d1f73ed6d92f04f28a390f108", "git_parents": ["564d8e2f4e28dcf0529086f6a2b095bdd79e62d1"], "node": "4cc89e5b3fc949beac0aa7a3da04526165d041b8", "parents": ["ed669ba8f6614024b5243255f3c47ba9050ff92f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1776774323, "git_changesets": ["929b3f8b7279019d1f73ed6d92f04f28a390f108"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25841": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sam Johnson \u003csam@scj.me\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2032196 - Use density-aware variables for search mode switcher padding.  a=dmeehan\n\nThis will probably be redone by bug 1826841, but this patch prevents regressing the compact density in 151 by using existing appropriate density-aware variables. With normal density, these variables have the same values that were already effective here, so there is no visual change.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294860\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295457\n", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/urlbar-searchbar.css"], "git_node": "e53cd5fd3a0b55470fda29cdd7c5b0d29f3c4f51", "git_parents": ["929b3f8b7279019d1f73ed6d92f04f28a390f108"], "node": "ff222b49495b80fcb638c09fbfcb13a70739b4dc", "parents": ["4cc89e5b3fc949beac0aa7a3da04526165d041b8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1776774363, "git_changesets": ["e53cd5fd3a0b55470fda29cdd7c5b0d29f3c4f51"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25842": {"changesets": [{"author": "az \u003cazebrowski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2031958 - Fix Solaris/GCC -Wincompatible-pointer-types build error in ffvpx parser_list.c  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295104\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295301\n", "files": ["media/ffvpx/libavcodec/parser_list.c"], "git_node": "55ad620da7c0e03292be2facc8320e2060ae6d57", "git_parents": ["e53cd5fd3a0b55470fda29cdd7c5b0d29f3c4f51"], "node": "9a79e1423065d722470ee0608fe64910bef34d79", "parents": ["ff222b49495b80fcb638c09fbfcb13a70739b4dc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1776774442, "git_changesets": ["55ad620da7c0e03292be2facc8320e2060ae6d57"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25843": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@lando.moz.tools\u003e", "branch": "tags-unified", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 1a6c5c6f11fca486436075d92fd82d51f706c775 with FIREFOX_150_0_RELEASE a=tagging CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": "251472d04f1b25cb6b349bc19d8a