er": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25884": {"changesets": [{"author": "Matthew Gregan \u003ckinetik@flim.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2030747 - r=media-playback-reviewers,padenot a=dmeehan\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295939\n", "files": ["dom/media/AudioConverter.cpp", "dom/media/AudioConverter.h"], "git_node": "c16135606fdbe7156efa7be555955c6e1c820090", "git_parents": ["11dec65ab768e2980f69712f4480d8878a1d1772"], "node": "19812c0cb7578c16c067216c81607f60808a143d", "parents": ["de82ba65695579237d2c809adb8f889382302234"], "tags": []}], "date": 1776947614, "git_changesets": ["c16135606fdbe7156efa7be555955c6e1c820090"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25885": {"changesets": [{"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2028526 - Clear SpeechTaskChild::mActor when SpeechSynthesisRequestChild is destroyed.  a=dmeehan\n\nMirrors the parent-side destructor. Without this, actor destruction paths\nother than RecvOnEnd (e.g. AncestorDeletion during IPC subtree teardown)\nleave SpeechTaskChild holding a dangling pointer, causing a UAF when\nspeechSynthesis.cancel() is subsequently called.\n\nAlso replace MOZ_ASSERT(mActor) in Pause/Resume/Cancel/ForceEnd with\nnull checks, matching the existing pattern in SetAudioOutputVolume.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295325\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295839\n", "files": ["dom/media/webspeech/synth/ipc/SpeechSynthesisChild.cpp"], "git_node": "fe16230c5c7a6d3f0858323648470e84a261cf5c", "git_parents": ["c16135606fdbe7156efa7be555955c6e1c820090"], "node": "da131c1b4ae7daa04cffa642bedf455d16878f23", "parents": ["19812c0cb7578c16c067216c81607f60808a143d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1776947656, "git_changesets": ["fe16230c5c7a6d3f0858323648470e84a261cf5c"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25886": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2029505 - Don't cache selection in IMEContentObserver.  a=dmeehan\n\nThe selection controller might be recreated without editor recreation\nitself. This could already realistically happen before bug 2016280 as\nfar as I can tell.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295508\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295956\n", "files": ["dom/base/test/chrome.toml", "dom/base/test/test_sendSelectionSetEvent_after_reframe.html", "dom/events/IMEContentObserver.cpp", "dom/events/IMEContentObserver.h"], "git_node": "405e434dccc62507280759f8b2178fee2f1d7c18", "git_parents": ["fe16230c5c7a6d3f0858323648470e84a261cf5c"], "node": "4540211ce843fae89584d5e4a071be0dd72e11eb", "parents": ["da131c1b4ae7daa04cffa642bedf455d16878f23"], "tags": []}], "date": 1776957422, "git_changesets": ["405e434dccc62507280759f8b2178fee2f1d7c18"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25887": {"changesets": [{"author": "Fred Chasen \u003cfchasen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2032227 - Add a locations subview for IP Protection.  a=dmeehan\n\n- Updates IPProtectionPanel to track multiple components and handle their states across different panelviews.\n- Adds and registers a new `IPProtectionLocationsElement` wrapper component.\n- Adds a `showLocationSelector()` method to switch views and listens for the IPProtection:UserShowLocations event from the UI to call it.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294532\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295976\n", "files": ["browser/base/content/appmenu-viewcache.inc.xhtml", "browser/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionPanel.sys.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/ipprotection-customelements.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/ipprotection-locations.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/jar.mn", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_ipprotection_panel.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/head.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProtectionPanel.js"], "git_node": "44df4eb7b9f49980a5734150bf1a3c8df7d42409", "git_parents": ["405e434dccc62507280759f8b2178fee2f1d7c18"], "node": "bfa51adb440b8f56fd6bbe818f33d1020a481573", "parents": ["4540211ce843fae89584d5e4a071be0dd72e11eb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1776957474, "git_changesets": ["44df4eb7b9f49980a5734150bf1a3c8df7d42409"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25888": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2033732 - Make `HTMLEditUtils::IsReplacedElement()` stop using `HTMLEditUtils::IsFormWidgetElement()`  a=dmeehan\n\nA form widget element does not mean it's a replaced element. So, it\nshould check each tag name instead. Additionally, it's the last user of\n`HTMLEditUtils::IsFormWidgetElement()` so that we can get rid of it.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295731\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296004\n", "files": ["editor/libeditor/HTMLEditUtils.cpp", "editor/libeditor/HTMLEditUtils.h", "editor/libeditor/gtest/TestHTMLEditUtils.cpp", "testing/web-platform/tests/editing/data/insertparagraph.js"], "git_node": "64ec3557a5b0489b710f97433007a4376a19e7c1", "git_parents": ["44df4eb7b9f49980a5734150bf1a3c8df7d42409"], "node": "c6467833306fa3212fcd3f8cfcfdc286de66539b", "parents": ["bfa51adb440b8f56fd6bbe818f33d1020a481573"], "tags": []}], "date": 1776957550, "git_changesets": ["64ec3557a5b0489b710f97433007a4376a19e7c1"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "25889": {"changesets": [{"author": "Reem H \u003c42309026+reemhamz@users.noreply.github.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2031669 - Customization button Nova update.  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294585\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296009\n", "files": ["browser/extensio