 that lives in the atom zone.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296441\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297356\n", "files": ["js/public/HeapAPI.h", "js/src/gc/WeakMap.h", "js/src/jit/ABIFunctionList-inl.h", "js/src/jit/CodeGenerator.cpp", "js/src/jit/CompileWrappers.cpp", "js/src/jit/CompileWrappers.h", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.h"], "git_node": "16f882a0229469b7fdf4849abf0ab9ccdec1fc61", "git_parents": ["5cce58baf5097b03e5f396751e8200a0101fb91a"], "node": "a2cd9648067afd1ae504fd7fdd31ef5bd4e6173a", "parents": ["8e40555c81be1624e6a92ea927353ff60e320af9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777551841, "git_changesets": ["16f882a0229469b7fdf4849abf0ab9ccdec1fc61"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26046": {"changesets": [{"author": "unknown \u003cdaparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2029240: Part 1 - Fix FxBackup removal of stale staging items  a=dmeehan\n\nThere was a missing `.path` reference in #prepareStagingFolder that caused\nfiles to not actually get deleted.  It was also doing some file access on the\nmain thread.  This fixes those.  We had tests that were supposed to check that\nfunctionality but this little bit was papers over for testing, so it wasn't\ncaught.  This patch adds a test that would catch the failure.\n\nThis patch also updates the regex in the test to match a more specific error\ncode, but this is just for clarity in the old test and is unrelated to this\nbug.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294550\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297463\n", "files": ["browser/components/backup/BackupService.sys.mjs", "browser/components/backup/tests/xpcshell/test_BackupService.js"], "git_node": "11a6ed4ebdd3da58a3878a8bd87e1eee2b57d0a8", "git_parents": ["16f882a0229469b7fdf4849abf0ab9ccdec1fc61"], "node": "5ce51f19a28c3796b3c471cc7700b15ddcbb4cc5", "parents": ["a2cd9648067afd1ae504fd7fdd31ef5bd4e6173a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "unknown \u003cdaparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2029240: Part 2 - Limit FxBackup file system error tests to Windows  a=dmeehan\n\nExcept for Windows, supported OSs allow unlinking opened files, so this case\ndoes not fail there.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294551\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297464\n", "files": ["browser/components/backup/tests/xpcshell/test_BackupService.js"], "git_node": "22467e56d7df9590ff523c7bcf1f334f1fc7745d", "git_parents": ["11a6ed4ebdd3da58a3878a8bd87e1eee2b57d0a8"], "node": "1c7c3c12f41884f0efe1544d1cec7cf229ba73e0", "parents": ["5ce51f19a28c3796b3c471cc7700b15ddcbb4cc5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777551892, "git_changesets": ["11a6ed4ebdd3da58a3878a8bd87e1eee2b57d0a8", "22467e56d7df9590ff523c7bcf1f334f1fc7745d"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26047": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jason Prickett \u003cjprickett@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2032544 - Add isNonStubFirstRun Nimbus targeting attribute for first-run enrollment on Mac, Linux, and MSIX  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295705\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297473\n", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/asrouter/docs/targeting-attributes.md", "browser/components/asrouter/tests/unit/TargetingDocs.test.js", "toolkit/components/nimbus/lib/ExperimentManager.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/nimbus/lib/RemoteSettingsExperimentLoader.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/nimbus/test/NimbusTestUtils.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/nimbus/test/unit/test_ExperimentManager_context.js"], "git_node": "579421577a051dbd88b992cea370d5b8b30fc33d", "git_parents": ["22467e56d7df9590ff523c7bcf1f334f1fc7745d"], "node": "b9369573f5061e7bb79a176294b6b700c043ed44", "parents": ["1c7c3c12f41884f0efe1544d1cec7cf229ba73e0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777551958, "git_changesets": ["579421577a051dbd88b992cea370d5b8b30fc33d"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26048": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kelly Cochrane \u003ckcochrane@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2030772 - Fix for intermittent test failure in browser/components/sidebar/tests/browser/browser_bookmarks_keyboard_navigation.js  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296210\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297487\n", "files": ["browser/components/sidebar/tests/browser/browser_bookmarks_keyboard_navigation.js"], "git_node": "163e3c9e00cf7e3e907c55453c40c69c12072fab", "git_parents": ["579421577a051dbd88b992cea370d5b8b30fc33d"], "node": "b0dc2c5bbe6b6b9bc3374278893c7e96346e700b", "parents": ["b9369573f5061e7bb79a176294b6b700c043ed44"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kelly Cochrane \u003ckcochrane@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2030988 - Fix for intermittent browser/components/sidebar/tests/browser/browser_bookmarks_keyboard_navigation.js  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297077\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297488\n", "files": ["browser/components/sidebar/sidebar-bookmark-list.mjs"], "git_node": "71b3141a1691a2ede92489c436913a34c74535b9", "git_parents": ["163e3c9e00cf7e3e907c55453c40c69c12072fab"], "node": "15fc7bce508c5a0f26b10b8e8e759b8edba79642", "parents": ["b0dc2c5bbe6b6b9bc3374278893c7e96346e700b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777552094, "git_changesets": ["163e3c9e00cf7e3e907c55453c40c69c12072fab", "71b3141a1691a2ede92489c436913a34c74535b9"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26049": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2031881 - Add new PlatformPipeReader type,  a=dmeehan\n\nThis is a new API which is intended to be used by code which wants to\nperform async reads from native filesystem pipes. This does not support\nasync reads from \"regular\" files, as those are not compatible with\nepoll.\n\nCurrently the API uses an owned buffer which is filled on the IPC I/O\nthread, and read from on the user's thread. This is technically only\nnecessary for Windows (as non-Windows OSes could directly invoke read\nduring nsIInputStream::read method), This is because overlapped I/O on\nWindows requires that the buffer be kept alive throughout the async\noperation. So far I have made the call to always use the buffer for API\nsupport consistency, but we could potentially change that behaviour.\n\nThe actual system file handle management is largely isolated to the\nPlatformPipeLink type within the .cpp file. This is done to allow the\nlifecycle of the nsIInputStream instance to be disconnected from the\nlifecycle of the underlying pipe, as things like the buffer need to be\nkept alive potentially longer than the stream to avoid issues on Windows\n& handle cancelling I/O on destruction.\n\nCurrently there is no way to use this type with a shared file handle,\nthe file handle must be owned by the PlatformPipeLink.\n\nPrevious versions of this patch contained a PlatformPipeWriter type as\nwell, but that had some issues with lifecycle which I haven't yet\nfigured out yet, and turns out to not be necessary for the WebSerial\nwork right now, so are being left to a follow-up.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294317\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297496\n", "files": ["xpcom/io/AsyncPlatformPipes.cpp", "xpcom/io/AsyncPlatformPipes.h", "xpcom/io/moz.build", "xpcom/tests/gtest/TestAsyncPlatformPipes.cpp", "xpcom/tests/gtest/moz.build"], "git_node": "e7bbe68b642d1344dec696ad096aeecb10f0dfd0", "git_parents": ["71b3141a1691a2ede92489c436913a34c74535b9"], "node": "31f68296aa55ea66582f756b2f06b499331deffc", "parents": ["15fc7bce508c5a0f26b10b8e8e759b8edba79642"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Greg Stoll \u003cgstoll@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2021345 - make WebSerial reads asynchronous  a=dmeehan\n\nNote that this relies on the new PlatformPipeReader class added for\nbug 2031881. Using this and NS_AsyncCopy() means that we no longer have\nto poll for new data from serial devices, which means we're faster to\nreceive that data and also yields better power usage.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294690\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297497\n", "files": ["dom/webserial/PosixSerialPlatformService.cpp", "dom/webserial/PosixSerialPlatformService.h", "dom/webserial/SerialPlatformService.cpp", "dom/webserial/SerialPlatformService.h", "dom/webserial/SerialPortParent.cpp", "dom/webserial/SerialPortParent.h", "dom/webserial/SerialPortPumps.cpp", "dom/webserial/SerialPortPumps.h", "dom/webserial/TestSerialPlatformService.cpp", "dom/webserial/TestSerialPlatformService.h", "dom/webserial/Win32SerialPlatformService.cpp", "dom/webserial/Win32SerialPlatformService.h"], "git_node": "79812a2681ba3301ead2100e6e63477cd33f8d17", "git_parents": ["e7bbe68b642d1344dec696ad096aeecb10f0dfd0"], "node": "3ff6f51ed3df9f78c5c2f2a5d0ea8598d64956a8", "parents": ["31f68296aa55ea66582f756b2f06b499331deffc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777553197, "git_changesets": ["e7bbe68b642d1344dec696ad096aeecb10f0dfd0", "79812a2681ba3301ead2100e6e63477cd33f8d17"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26050": {"changesets": [{"author": "Irene Ni \u003cini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2033927 - Newtab Nova privacy link color and focus styling fix.  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295703\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297516\n", "files": ["browser/extensions/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/Navigation/_Navigation.scss", "browser/extensions/newtab/css/activity-stream.css", "browser/extensions/newtab/css/nova/activity-stream.css"], "git_node": "89e3d45b5c99f45b9d0e66c9c96a53136d37a3a2", "git_parents": ["79812a2681ba3301ead2100e6e63477cd33f8d17"], "node": "eca7501236e3c6b1c176b56c037c5f38e708fa26", "parents": ["3ff6f51ed3df9f78c5c2f2a5d0ea8598d64956a8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777553248, "git_changesets": ["89e3d45b5c99f45b9d0e66c9c96a53136d37a3a2"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26051": {"changesets": [{"author": "Artur Iunusov \u003caiunusov@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022722 - LoggingInfo: validate serial numbers,  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D293472\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297587\n", "files": ["dom/indexedDB/ActorsParent.cpp"], "git_node": "7cf13245e05bf4299fa20af4a58f7cb2f55bf2b3", "git_parents": ["89e3d45b5c99f45b9d0e66c9c96a53136d37a3a2"], "node": "0d610b925f0843b331d6ecfb4750289be613eae6", "parents": ["eca7501236e3c6b1c176b56c037c5f38e708fa26"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777553594, "git_changesets": ["7cf13245e05bf4299fa20af4a58f7cb2f55bf2b3"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26052": {"changesets": [{"author": "smayya \u003csmayya@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2035801 - Disable the pref security.ssl3.ecdhe_ecdsa_aes_128_sha for release  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297314\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297523\n", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml"], "git_node": "146d678bca50de10b6d8d6addbc6937b8afd3d79", "git_parents": ["7cf13245e05bf4299fa20af4a58f7cb2f55bf2b3"], "node": "22ddefe0e98f1f2109db973ec7a67d89c4eaa8a1", "parents": ["0d610b925f0843b331d6ecfb4750289be613eae6"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777553655, "git_changesets": ["146d678bca50de10b6d8d6addbc6937b8afd3d79"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26053": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2034897 - Fix aspect-ratio handling in ComputeSizeWithIntrinsicDimensions.  a=dmeehan\n\nPrefer aspect-ratio to the tentative BSize if we have both tentative\nISize and BSize.\n\nAlso make auto aspect-ratio handling a bit more explicit.\n\nTo prevent some regressions, we need to:\n\n * Fix size-containment aspect ratio for \u003cembed\u003e (nsSubDocumentFrame).\n * Fix RasterImage::GetIntrinsicRatio with uneven ratios.\n * Avoid SVG root from using the aspect ratio from the viewbox, see\n   bug 2035918.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296982\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297604\n", "files": ["image/RasterImage.cpp", "layout/generic/nsContainerFrame.cpp", "layout/generic/nsIFrame.cpp", "layout/generic/nsSubDocumentFrame.cpp", "layout/generic/nsSubDocumentFrame.h", "layout/svg/SVGOuterSVGFrame.cpp", "layout/svg/tests/test_embed_sizing.html", "servo/ports/geckolib/cbindgen.toml", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-grid/alignment/grid-item-aspect-ratio-stretch-4.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-sizing/aspect-ratio/replaced-element-043.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-sizing/aspect-ratio/replaced-element-044.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-sizing/aspect-ratio/replaced-element-045.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-sizing/aspect-ratio/replaced-element-046.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-sizing/svg-intrinsic-size-007.tentative.html.ini"], "git_node": "daa11c20babddc6c0b4abd19ea69c4c8e4e8af9c", "git_parents": ["146d678bca50de10b6d8d6addbc6937b8afd3d79"], "node": "02204e718495531be4850b6bce3d3a40fd7a3fce", "parents": ["22ddefe0e98f1f2109db973ec7a67d89c4eaa8a1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777553781, "git_changesets": ["daa11c20babddc6c0b4abd19ea69c4c8e4e8af9c"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26054": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2032328 - Update FinalizationRegistry targets on transplant  a=dmeehan\n\nThe same as for WeakRefs, we need to move FinalizationRegistry records when\ntheir target is transplanted.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296688\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297616\n", "files": ["js/src/gc/FinalizationObservers.cpp", "js/src/gc/FinalizationObservers.h", "js/src/gc/GCRuntime.h", "js/src/jit-test/tests/gc/transplant-finalization-registry-targets.js", "js/src/jsapi.cpp"], "git_node": "2f8052c4d1da81d2250e9c16265a9dbe800584a1", "git_parents": ["daa11c20babddc6c0b4abd19ea69c4c8e4e8af9c"], "node": "2bbcd68a0f8fb2d0a3595abc99b76cdbbeff3f94", "parents": ["02204e718495531be4850b6bce3d3a40fd7a3fce"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777553848, "git_changesets": ["2f8052c4d1da81d2250e9c16265a9dbe800584a1"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26055": {"changesets": [{"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2027159 - Fix for DecodedStream. r=media-playback-reviewers,padenot a=dmeehan\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294822\n", "files": ["dom/media/mediasink/DecodedStream.cpp", "dom/media/mediasink/DecodedStream.h"], "git_node": "21db70298bd8bdf60540223d68c100c49f211cda", "git_parents": ["2f8052c4d1da81d2250e9c16265a9dbe800584a1"], "node": "eeabef576ffa3e2a56e2466cfc74c9095d893dee", "parents": ["2bbcd68a0f8fb2d0a3595abc99b76cdbbeff3f94"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2027159 - Fix for DecodedStream. r=media-playback-reviewers,padenot a=dmeehan\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294823\n", "files": ["dom/media/MediaDecoder.cpp", "dom/media/mediasink/DecodedStream.cpp"], "git_node": "afd70d3fa16a330656c437dde7a3cef57d448562", "git_parents": ["21db70298bd8bdf60540223d68c100c49f211cda"], "node": "ef8d064d058105af555438380e75c09fe9b0979a", "parents": ["eeabef576ffa3e2a56e2466cfc74c9095d893dee"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L