rential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297664\n", "files": ["browser/components/tabbrowser/content/tabgroup-menu.js", "browser/components/tabbrowser/metrics.yaml", "browser/components/tabbrowser/test/browser/tabs/browser_tab_groups_telemetry.js"], "git_node": "335ce3926d7c226f259043feb41c734e03f3b234", "git_parents": ["ea04df46e0346388cfe5145bf162a39ff96839a8"], "node": "a269180c70ba0fd58399a22b6345623c6f445976", "parents": ["01783567a611eca8e507a13d6029b3814f953590"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777567123, "git_changesets": ["335ce3926d7c226f259043feb41c734e03f3b234"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26062": {"changesets": [{"author": "Florian Zia \u003cfzia@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2030782 - Fix selecting non-heuristic smartbar chat suggestion by keyboard  a=dmeehan\n\nAddresses an issue where selecting a non-heuristic chat suggestions by keyboard and pressing Enter cleared the smartbar instead of submitting the query. Non-heuristic chat results are results labeled with \u201cAsk\u201d when the default intent is not chat.\n\nAlso fixes bug 2031245.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D293505\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297663\n", "files": ["browser/components/aiwindow/ui/actors/AISmartBarChild.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/actors/AISmartBarParent.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/components/ai-window/ai-window.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_aiwindow_smartbar.js", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_aiwindow_smartbar_ask.js", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_aiwindow_smartbar_context_chips.js", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_aiwindow_smartbar_telemetry.js", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/head.js", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarController.sys.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarProviderAiChat.sys.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/content/SmartbarInput.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_engagement.js"], "git_node": "363dcfa127e94f7fe9171fb7b668996b9d08f7ef", "git_parents": ["335ce3926d7c226f259043feb41c734e03f3b234"], "node": "a9161101c4d4608bed5400bdc28bd9b749990d08", "parents": ["a269180c70ba0fd58399a22b6345623c6f445976"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777567170, "git_changesets": ["363dcfa127e94f7fe9171fb7b668996b9d08f7ef"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26063": {"changesets": [{"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2035209: Fix nargs computation  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297137\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297677\n", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/ion/bug2035209.js", "js/src/jit/IonCacheIRCompiler.cpp"], "git_node": "cf180a13db0ffc9fef7123f829d342b339ce3ddb", "git_parents": ["363dcfa127e94f7fe9171fb7b668996b9d08f7ef"], "node": "071b134f13910dc44555fadfac928839fcbfda0d", "parents": ["a9161101c4d4608bed5400bdc28bd9b749990d08"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777567218, "git_changesets": ["cf180a13db0ffc9fef7123f829d342b339ce3ddb"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26064": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2028579 - Part 1: Remove IProtocol::CanRecv,  a=dmeehan\n\nLooking at the existing callers, it seems like basically all of them\nactually wanted `CanSend()`, and didn't want this function. This method\nis misleading, as it is just a value which returns `true` until\n`ActorDestroy()` has been called.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294218\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297694\n", "files": ["dom/base/nsFrameLoader.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserBridgeHost.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserBridgeHost.h", "dom/ipc/BrowserHost.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserHost.h", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/BrowserParent.h", "dom/ipc/InProcessImpl.cpp", "dom/ipc/RemoteBrowser.h", "dom/media/ipc/RemoteDecoderParent.cpp", "ipc/glue/Endpoint.cpp", "ipc/glue/ProtocolUtils.cpp", "ipc/glue/ProtocolUtils.h", "netwerk/protocol/websocket/WebSocketChannelParent.cpp"], "git_node": "8f981288a063b7d59f1b78eadd102900b96a4f16", "git_parents": ["cf180a13db0ffc9fef7123f829d342b339ce3ddb"], "node": "98a5aa3559976930031a9ab9d6b260085894e1c3", "parents": ["071b134f13910dc44555fadfac928839fcbfda0d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2028579 - Part 2: Doom subtree earlier in Recv__delete__,  a=dmeehan\n\nThis simplifies the behaviour a bit more by making the structure of the\nIPDL protocol's lifecycle more explicit.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D294219\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297695\n", "files": ["ipc/glue/ProtocolUtils.cpp", "ipc/glue/ProtocolUtils.h", "ipc/ipdl/ipdl/lower.py"], "git_node": "b55d86906672e04f3d28ebfdcb1fd7782247d0b8", "git_parents": ["8f981288a063b7d59f1b78eadd102900b96a4f16"], "node": "e368d6c4beeddc4188fb0de257b46f7bda9dee3a", "parents": ["98a5aa3559976930031a9ab9d6b260085894e1c3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777574385, "git_changesets": ["8f981288a063b7d59f1b78eadd102900b96a4f16", "b55d86906672e04f3d28ebfdcb1fd7782247d0b8"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26065": {"changesets": [{"author": "Reem H \u003c42309026+reemhamz@users.noreply.github.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2034688 - Fix wallpaper from disappearing when newtabWallpapers.user.enabled pref lands for users.  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296307\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297662\n", "files": ["browser/extensions/newtab/content-src/components/CustomizeMenu/ContentSection/ContentSection.jsx", "browser/extensions/newtab/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js", "browser/extensions/newtab/lib/Wallpapers/WallpaperFeed.sys.mjs", "browser/extensions/newtab/test/xpcshell/test_WallpaperFeed.js"], "git_node": "9f39bc99bd7e2d0c946e04fec5cabd510b4fa352", "git_parents": ["b55d86906672e04f3d28ebfdcb1fd7782247d0b8"], "node": "979775040990b3ad2ee9f474c02abe0194f48ccc", "parents": ["e368d6c4beeddc4188fb0de257b46f7bda9dee3a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777574445, "git_changesets": ["9f39bc99bd7e2d0c946e04fec5cabd510b4fa352"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26066": {"changesets": [{"author": "Matthew Tighe \u003cmatthewdtighe@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2025637 - swallow exceptions while retrieving Autofill system service  a=dmeehan\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297721\n", "files": ["mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/autofill/src/main/java/mozilla/components/feature/autofill/AutofillUseCases.kt", "mobile/android/android-components/components/feature/autofill/src/test/java/mozilla/components/feature/autofill/AutofillUseCasesTest.kt"], "git_node": "74d1b993f3b0f62799dc570da3568088a70e5678", "git_parents": ["9f39bc99bd7e2d0c946e04fec5cabd510b4fa352"], "node": "a7ca8fd60e537005508dae69b758722d9e8723f3", "parents": ["979775040990b3ad2ee9f474c02abe0194f48ccc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777584355, "git_changesets": ["74d1b993f3b0f62799dc570da3568088a70e5678"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26067": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2034798 - Refactor gfx blocklist macros to prevent common mistakes.  a=dmeehan\n\nThis patch adds static asserts to prevent allowlist statuses to be\nused with non-allowlist features, as well as prevent retired\nfeatures from being used. It also removes the name/ID split for\nmost features where they are the same.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296378\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297738\n", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/data/test_gfxBlocklist.json", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/data/test_gfxBlocklist_AllOS.json", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/rs-blocklist/test_gfxBlocklist_Version.js", "widget/GfxDriverInfo.h", "widget/GfxInfoBase.cpp", "widget/GfxInfoBase.h", "widget/GfxInfoFeatureDefs.inc", "widget/nsIGfxInfo.idl"], "git_node": "8fab1078028972fe16438f6d02afb48c354f6f9c", "git_parents": ["74d1b993f3b0f62799dc570da3568088a70e5678"], "node": "d63e8ae309d36c8a31eef44cba92e8ea8388955a", "parents": ["a7ca8fd60e537005508dae69b758722d9e8723f3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1777584401, "git_changesets": ["8fab1078028972fe16438f6d02afb48c354f6f9c"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26068": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Streich \u003csstreich@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2031686 - Expose a Country-List in the IPProtectionServerlist  a=dmeehan\n\nThis adds a getter for countries() that provides the data needed to show the location picker subview:\n-\u003e A list of countries with their ISO code, so Intl can be used to get a Translated Version.\nThe Reccomended location is omitted here.\n\nFor the reccomended server the UI has 2 options, either handle the Reccomended location as an omition, by passing \"\" or null.\nOr they can explicitly request that location by requesting RECOMMENDED_COUNTRY_CODE.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295281\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297701\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/ipprotection/IPPProxyManager.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionServerlist.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProtectionServerlist.js"], "git_node": "a174f1aba7f1b2e5919c564b90a80ba20281432e", "git_parents": ["8fab1078028972fe16438f6d02afb48c354f6f9c"], "node": "19727a209f419ce5422dbef31ee56f3cc73575a3", "parents": ["d63e8ae309d36c8a31eef44cba92e8ea8388955a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Streich \u003csstreich@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2031687 - Add a CountryCode argument to IPPProxyManager.start  a=dmeehan\n\nThis adds  a new param string country to IPProxyManager.start():\nAn Optional ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code to route through. When omitted, the recommended (anycast) location is used.\n\nThis allows IPProtectionPanel.sys.mjs to set the selected server when activating.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295282\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297702\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/ipprotection/IPPProxyManager.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProxyManager.js"], "git_node": "ef09b409596d260fb9b8d5eb8f2b17016178248c", "git_parents": ["a174f1aba7f1b2e5919c564b90a80ba20281432e"], "node": "6acce54e0ac74bf68b456f2fb786467ac37a6a75", "parents": ["19727a209f419ce5422dbef31ee56f3cc73575a3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Artem Popov \u003cart@artfwo.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2033804 - Create an IPProxyManager::switch function.  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295828\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297703\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/ipprotection/IPPProxyManager.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProxyManager.js"], "git_node": "790d6dca58fcbe45790b2d9e2a690ac8de78ee42", "git_parents": ["ef09b409596d260fb9b8d5eb8f2b17016178248c"], "node": "48a34ddd1453fcc384d64c4d1c89d62ffe94ef50", "parents": ["6acce54e0ac74bf68b456f2fb786467ac37a6a75"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fred Chasen \u003cfchasen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2033616 - Add locationsList to IPProtectionPanel state and set location from a pref  a=dmeehan\n\n- Set the `IPProtectionPanel` locationsList state from `IPProtectionServerlist`\n- Add `browser.ipProtection.egressLocation` pref for the current selected location.\n- Pass the current location on proxy start.\n- Remove `egressLocationEnabled` feature flag check but keep the pref for use in the UI if needed.\n- Remove the previous location status UI\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295414\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297704\n", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionPanel.sys.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/ipprotection-status-box.css", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/ipprotection-status-box.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/ipprotection-status-card.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_ipprotection_bandwidth_precision.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_ipprotection_status_card.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/head.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProtectionPanel.js", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/docs/Preferences.rst"], "git_node": "6c0539b1d31e2909ba7b657d0035a2fd4b4a734d", "git_parents": ["790d6dca58fcbe45790b2d9e2a690ac8de78ee42"], "node": "f5c7a39cb1afd8fa7ac7b8111ba26323d6185477", "parents": ["48a34ddd1453fcc384d64c4d1c89d62ffe94ef50"], "tags": []}, {"author": "kpatenio \u003ckpatenio@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2033146 \u2014 implement location picker list.  a=dmeehan\n\nThis patch renders the list of locations for the location picker subview.\n\n- Adds a new component locations-list\n- Adds tests for verifying the contents\n\nKeyboard navigation order to match our spec will be addressed in a follow-up task.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295987\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297705\n", "files": ["browser/base/content/appmenu-viewcache.inc.xhtml", "browser/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionPanel.sys.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/ipprotection-locations.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/locations-list.css", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/locations-list.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/jar.mn", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser.toml", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_ipprotection_locations_list.js"], "git_node": "c4e7cea9468b6831946efc726f4a4c6a07edb44e", "git_parents": ["6c0539b1d31e2909ba7b657d0035a2fd4b4a734d"], "node": "27e1e5d0a75d638417323d7604f39f1387ae0cde", "parents": ["f5c7a39cb1afd8fa7ac7b8111ba26323d6185477"], "tags": []}, {"author": "kpatenio \u003ckpatenio@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2034575 \u2014 Alphabetically sort country list in location picker.  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296818\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297706\n", "files": ["browser/components/ipprotection/content/locations-list.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_ipprotection_locations_list.js"], "git_node": "0d7385693d54be9147aee1b560872deb47ab51a1", "git_parents": ["c4e7cea9468b6831946efc726f4a4c6a07edb44e"], "node": "58a37015ac81c570957e79cb57ac8bbfa457a247", "parents": ["27e1e5d0a75d638417323d7604f39f1387ae0cde"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rebecca King \u003crking@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2033135 - Add moz-promo to ipprotection locations subview -  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D296444\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D297707\n", "files": ["browser/components/ipprotection/assets/mozilla-vpn-promo.svg", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/ipprotection-locations.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/locations-list.css", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/locations-list.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/locations-subview.css", "browser/components/ipprotection/jar.mn", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_ipp