ng and bolster tests  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D298702\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D299751\n", "files": ["browser/components/aboutwelcome/tests/browser/browser_aboutwelcome_screen_targeting.js", "browser/components/asrouter/modules/OnboardingMessageProvider.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "7fbd18af1293387ca03d5bbdff289cad8dc3d461", "git_parents": ["9213f2a354b7713b3579e4879c17e1a4f415d1ec"], "node": "3265e658be953286c748fa093056b09063458939", "parents": ["67f6c15a9e56a65452644d9f515b5a2d19a67895"], "tags": []}], "date": 1778523568, "git_changesets": ["7fbd18af1293387ca03d5bbdff289cad8dc3d461"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "26287": {"changesets": [{"author": "kpatenio \u003ckpatenio@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2037542 \u2014 ipprotection locations subview keyboard and other accessibility improvements.  a=dmeehan\n\nThis patch ensures:\n- pressing left arrow key always closes the location selector subview\n- pressing right arrow key closes the location subview for RTL\n- first location gets focus if the subview was opened via keyboard activation\n- appropriate roles and aria labels for the locations list to improve screen reader use\n- closing the subview with the keyboard puts focus back on the location button in the main panel\n- restores button borders for location items, but only if in HCM or forced colors mode\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D298700\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D299768\n", "files": ["browser/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionPanel.sys.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/ipprotection-status-card.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/locations-list.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/content/locations-subview.css", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_ipprotection_locations_keyboard_navigation.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/t